               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-198" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-198" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-198" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-198" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS ROBERTS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a tailor, and live in the Poultry. On the 5th of March, between seven and eight o'clock in the evening, I was near my window—I heard a noise, and saw a pair of trowsers go off the rail—I ran out, and saw the prisoner with them—he went across the Poultry, and down Bucklersbury, where he was taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-199" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-199" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-199" type="surname" value="RUSHMER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-199" type="given" value="MARK"></interp>MARK RUSHMER</persName>
                  </hi>. I was passing, and saw the prisoner draw the trowsers and throw them over his shoulder—he crossed the street, and went down Bucklersbury, where he was stopped.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I went out to seek for employment, but could not get any—my mother was in great distress, without food or firing—I saw the trowsers, and it was a great temptation.</p>
